full_title: You're Losing Me (From The Vault) by Taylor Swift
title: You’re Losing Me (From The Vault)

description.plain:
“You’re Losing Me” is a From The Vault track of her tenth studio album, Midnights. At first, the track was available to purchase for 24 hours on Taylor’s website, then released only on a CD that was exclusively available to purchase at Swift’s 2023 The Eras Tour.

Six months after being released on CD, Swift announced that the song would be available on streaming platforms in November 29, 2023, as a “thank you” present to the fans, who made her Spotify’s Global Top Artist of 2023.

The song is rumored to be detailing Swift’s point of view in the breakup of her six-year-long relationship with British actor Joe Alwyn.

Interestingly, “You’re Losing Me” is also the second song in Swift’s discography to feature the sample of her own heartbeat — the first time she did it was on her 2014 single, “Wildest Dreams.”
